### Pre-Commit Security Checklist

**BEFORE EVERY COMMIT, verify:**

```powershell
# 1. Search for potential secrets (PowerShell)
git diff --cached | Select-String -Pattern "(password|secret|key|token|credential)" -CaseSensitive:$false

# 2. Check for sensitive files (PowerShell)
git diff --cached --name-only | Select-String -Pattern "(.env|.keystore|.jks|.log)"

# 3. Review what you're committing
git diff --cached

# 4. Ensure .gitignore is working
git status --ignored
```

**Manual checks:**
- [ ] No hardcoded passwords in code
- [ ] No API keys in source files
- [ ] No real email addresses in examples
- [ ] No account numbers or bank details
- [ ] No authentication tokens
- [ ] No log files being committed
- [ ] No test data with real user information
- [ ] .env files not tracked
- [ ] Firebase config files ignored
- [ ] Keystores not included

## Permission Handling

### Request Only Necessary Permissions
```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Request permission only when needed
async function requestCameraPermission(): Promise<boolean> {
  const { status } = await Camera.requestCameraPermissionsAsync();
  
  if (status !== 'granted') {
    // Explain why permission is needed
    Alert.alert(
      'Camera Permission',
      'Camera access is needed to scan animal tags.'
    );
    return false;
  }
  return true;
}
```

### Check Permissions Before Use
```typescript
async function scanTag(): Promise<void> {
  const hasPermission = await checkCameraPermission();
  if (!hasPermission) {
    throw new PermissionDeniedException('Camera permission required');
  }
  // Proceed with scanning
}
```

